<TITLE> AHM Moqbul Hossain is new IG prisons </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 3 (bdnews24.com)  Brigadier general AHM Moqbul Hossain has been appointed inspector general of prisons, said an establishment ministry order on Tuesday. A joint secretary and four deputy secretaries also saw transfers, said separate ministry orders. Major general Syed Fatemi Ahmed Rumi, director general of the Special Security Force during the last BNP-led government, has been made chairman of BIISS. Joint secretary Abu Bakar Siddique has been put in charge of appointment, promotion and deputation (APD) at the establishment ministry Deputy secretary for labour and employment Nasir Arif Mahmood, BRTC director Abdur Rouf and Dhaka WASA's chief revenue officer Khalid Mahmood have been transferred to the shipping ministry, the land ministry, and the economic division respectively. Omar Faruk, who was OSD at the 100-day employment generation programme under the food ministry, has been appointed project director of the Protection of Children at Risk programme under the social welfare ministry. bdnew
